1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,120
<i>I want people</i>
<i>To scream for me at the stage</i>

2
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,920
<i>Please accept me as an artist</i>

3
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,200
<i>I promise I'll do well</i>

4
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:43,360
Right now, Poona is about to record

5
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:44,960
- with Darathong Music!
- Yes.

6
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,840
My daughter

7
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:48,920
dreams of becoming a singer.

8
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,640
If it's not too much trouble,

9
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:51,800
‪PREVIOUS EPISODE

10
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,920
could you help her out?

11
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:59,440
<i>Can't stand it anymore. I want people</i>
<i>To scream for me at the stage</i>

12
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,320
Wasn't anyone told

13
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,600
that your recording today was canceled?

14
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:07,560
How long will she have to wait?

15
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:08,840
A couple of months.

16
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:12,960
What am I supposed to do while I wait?

17
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:17,240
I won't take advantage of you, Poona.

18
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:19,720
While waiting for the new song,

19
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:23,320
I'll have you work

20
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:26,360
as an intern at the company.

21
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:30,080
At least you'll get to learn
from a senior artist like Sornrak

22
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:32,840
about how to carry yourself

23
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,320
as a real singer.

24
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:45,200
Think of it as training before your debut.

25
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:47,480
Just like how artists train in Korea.

26
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,200
Is that a good idea, Poona?

27
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,360
Your talent is singing,

28
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:57,200
not working in an office.

29
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:01,840
Teacher, being an intern at our label

30
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:04,440
will give her the chance to go on shoots,
learn various roles,

31
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,240
and understand the life of a real artist.

32
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,640
- I'll do it.
- Poona!

33
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:56,200
I've made up my mind, Teacher.

34
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,280
I'll intern at the company

35
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,840
while I wait for my own song.

36
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,000
Good.

37
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,920
To be a singer at Darathong Music,

38
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,600
you need to understand things easily.

39
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,840
No fuss.

40
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,960
Poona.

41
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,760
To be honest,

42
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:37,480
I don't want you working
on anything other than singing.

43
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,840
It could cost you opportunities.

44
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:41,480
And if we follow what they're offering,

45
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:42,880
they might take advantage of you.

46
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,680
I don't want that to happen.

47
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:47,520
I'm sorry for making that decision.

48
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,720
The thing is…

49
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,200
What?

50
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:57,000
The teddy bear.

51
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:01,920
I think if I go to the company every day,

52
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,520
I'll have more chances
with the teddy bear.

53
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:06,080
I completely forgot about that.

54
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:10,720
Aunt Wilai and my dad, Phupha,

55
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,960
were falsely accused.

56
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,880
I'll do whatever I can to help.

57
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:20,200
I'm not trying to flatter you, Miss Maria.

58
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:23,360
If your first single is released,

59
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:26,640
it's definitely going to be a hit
and get millions of subscribers.

60
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:29,720
Let me know if there's a show booking.

61
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:33,280
I'd love to be a dancer.
The song is really fun to dance to.

62
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:36,000
- Can I dance too?
- Of course!

63
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:39,720
Miss Maria.

64
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,680
Would it be too much trouble

65
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:45,840
if I asked to hear you sing another hook?

66
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,600
Could you do that?

67
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:53,200
<i>Who owns this famous music label?</i>
<i>They say the boss</i>

68
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,640
<i>Is good looking</i>

69
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,360
<i>The singers of this label…</i>

70
00:06:57,440 --> 00:07:00,320
Wait. Can't you stand listening?

71
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,960
Maybe you're embarrassed.

72
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,880
Your recording got canceled.

73
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,160
I'll just laugh it off!

74
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:19,200
I'm happy for you, Maria,
that you got to record first,

75
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:23,800
even though
I was the one who won the competition.

76
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,480
Ouch!

77
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:30,760
That was a calm statement,
but it cuts deep, Miss Maria.

78
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,280
Sophie.

79
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:36,240
She probably knows your dad came

80
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:37,920
to ask Mr. Singha for help.

81
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:42,160
If you didn't say it, no one would know.

82
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:50,680
I don't know why Mr. Singha
suddenly changed his mind

83
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:53,560
and had me record instead of you.

84
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:58,080
I feel uncomfortable about it.

85
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:00,840
Oh well.

86
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:03,640
You can race boats,

87
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:07,600
but you can't race fate or destiny.

88
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:12,280
- True.
- Yeah!

89
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,240
But like I said,

90
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:17,200
you and I have always been competing.

91
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:20,120
This time, I won.

92
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:24,520
I became a singer first,

93
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:27,240
while you've already signed a contract

94
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:29,400
- for nothing.
- True, again.

95
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:33,720
If you can't afford food,
don't be shy, okay?

96
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:35,840
I'll help you out.

97
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:38,919
Wow!

98
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,360
- A true angel.
- Enough!

99
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:45,160
Even though Poona might have had
her song taken away shamelessly,

100
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:48,280
Mr. Sornrak will find her a new song.

101
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:50,760
The new song will suit her character

102
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,440
and vocal range, allowing her
to showcase her potential.

103
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:54,560
Right, Poona?

104
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:59,000
While waiting for the new song,

105
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,160
I'll come to the company every day

106
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:03,800
as an employee.

107
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:07,600
Even though I'm not singing or performing,

108
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,360
I'll have a steady salary
and live comfortably.

109
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:15,640
I won't need to rely on you, Maria.
Sorry about that.

110
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:18,520
How bold. Acting all grand.

111
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:21,720
What's your role in the company?

112
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:29,400
- What does it mean?
- I don't know. I'm not a foreigner.

113
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:33,400
Let's go. Don't pay attention to them.

114
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:37,160
I need to find out what costume means.
I have to know!

115
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:54,680
Boss Noo's crew is making moves today.

116
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,680
Something's definitely going on.

117
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:02,080
Today, Kamnan Pong is making a donation.

118
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:05,000
It might be related.

119
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:08,240
Hey, who's that?

120
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,880
Sergeant, let's split up here.

121
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,280
- Hurry and report to Captain Tom.
- Where are you going, Captain?

122
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:42,720
I'm going to track their movements.

123
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,160
- Go!
- Understood.

124
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:49,320
Hey, the boss sent me. It's time to go.

125
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:53,280
Hurry up.

126
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:56,840
Finish loading.

127
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:12,880
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

128
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:20,120
<i>As tough as a bar of steel</i>

129
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:25,080
<i>So many men chased after me</i>

130
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:28,240
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

131
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:32,440
<i>Never gave them a thought</i>

132
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:37,720
<i>But now, my heart is starting to weaken</i>

133
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:45,000
<i>From the very first time I saw him</i>
<i>My heart started to waver</i>

134
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:50,000
<i>What is it about this man?</i>

135
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:53,200
<i>Every time I see his face</i>

136
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:57,760
<i>My heart pounds</i>

137
00:11:58,680 --> 00:12:03,680
<i>Oh, my heart</i>

138
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:09,600
<i>Why can't you stay composed?</i>

139
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:19,520
This is a tape Phupha has kept.

140
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,960
You shouldn't have played it
without permission.

141
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:25,400
I wrote this song.

142
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,800
And the voice on the tape is mine.

143
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:34,080
It's unfortunate that Kamnan Pong
stopped the song from being released

144
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:36,840
after the accident

145
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:39,120
20 years ago.

146
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,800
I believe this song

147
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:45,240
would have been a big hit
if it had been promoted.

148
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,880
Do you know?

149
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:51,960
I wrote this song

150
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:54,920
as a tribute to a man.

151
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,240
You must be talking about Kamnan Pong.

152
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:02,880
Yes.

153
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,720
I wrote it for Kamnan Pong.

154
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:09,440
I heard you ran away from my brother
and went to him.

155
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:13,080
I guess that's how it is.

156
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,280
A singer like me

157
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:20,000
should marry the owner of a record label,

158
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:23,680
not your penniless brother, right?

159
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:26,840
Well, it's good

160
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,680
that Namtip married Phupha.

161
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:33,600
Even though she was a widow
with a child, Poona,

162
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:35,720
she was a wife

163
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:39,840
who was loyal only to my brother.

164
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:42,760
Unlike some people.

165
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:56,600
The fact that Poona
isn't Phupha's real child,

166
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,720
doesn't that trouble you?

167
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:06,000
Poona is a pitiful child.

168
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:11,440
She grew up with only her mother,

169
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:14,040
never knowing who her real father is.

170
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:17,640
The fact that Phupha took her in
as his daughter,

171
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:20,560
I would do the same.

172
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:23,440
Because if I were to abandon her,

173
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:26,200
she would have no one left.

174
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:28,440
Since growing up,

175
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:30,760
she's never known the truth about this,

176
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:34,480
so don't spread it around.

177
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,400
You can trust me.

178
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:41,240
All the secrets,

179
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:45,320
I'll keep them to myself.

180
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:51,960
I promise I won't reveal this to anyone.

181
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,760
It's time. Today is the anniversary

182
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,960
of Phupha and Namtip's death.

183
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,480
I'll meet Poona at the temple.

184
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,880
I know.

185
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:12,720
I've also made five-spice eggs,

186
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,720
Phupha's favorite dish,

187
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,720
and prepared it to offer to him.

188
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,400
I came today

189
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:22,560
because I'm taking you with me.

190
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:28,960
Alright, let's go then.

191
00:15:29,640 --> 00:15:30,680
Let's go together.

192
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:53,080
Alright, let's go to this room.

193
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:56,200
This is the wardrobe room.
I'd like you to pick out some clothes

194
00:15:56,280 --> 00:15:58,280
to see what style you like.

195
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:01,120
Once we finish mixing the song,
we'll shoot the MV.

196
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:03,880
You'll have a chance to prepare
before meeting with the designer.

197
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:07,320
Well, Mr. Sornrak,

198
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,840
will you help me pick out the clothes?

199
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,720
Actually, I'm busy today.

200
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:15,800
I have to help Kamnan Pong
distribute goods to the villagers.

201
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:19,240
Look around and pick what you like,
Maria. I'll leave now.

202
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,200
Take your time.

203
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,480
Miss Maria.

204
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:29,720
Don't bother picking out clothes.
It's wasting time.

205
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:32,000
- This isn't the right moment.
- Why?

206
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:35,240
Our chance to become famous,
even before the song is released, is here!

207
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:37,320
What are you talking about?
I don't get it.

208
00:16:37,880 --> 00:16:39,480
If you don't get it, just shut up!

209
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:42,760
Listen, I think today,

210
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:45,040
Mr. Sornrak is making a donation.

211
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:48,160
He'll definitely be going live
to create content.

212
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:50,560
Just think about it. While he's live,

213
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:54,680
if you suddenly appear next to him,

214
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:55,640
what will happen?

215
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:57,720
People will comment, saying,

216
00:16:57,800 --> 00:17:00,120
"This is the new celebrity couple!"

217
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:03,840
Miss Maria, you'd go viral for sure!

218
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:05,520
Exactly!

219
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:08,400
Then who's going to create the buzz?

220
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,800
Me.

221
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:10,839
And you too.

222
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,160
Let's comment together and create a buzz,

223
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,920
so people see it often.

224
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,920
After that, the buzz
will happen on its own!

225
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:22,160
Sophie, why are you so smart?

226
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:24,040
Not as smart as you.

227
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:26,319
You sure know what to say.

228
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:29,880
- Let's go. Forget the clothes.
- Yes.

229
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:33,080
- Let's follow Mr. Sornrak.
- Let's go!

230
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:39,080
They're here.

231
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:46,760
- Let me help.
- Thanks.

232
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,160
Uncle, my song…

233
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,720
It's okay, Poona.

234
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:55,600
Even though the song was taken from you,

235
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:58,040
just consider it wasn't meant
to be your song.

236
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:00,920
Some singers

237
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,920
may get a good song,
but no matter how they sing it,

238
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,080
it doesn't become a hit.

239
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:07,200
Meanwhile, some singers,

240
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:09,600
even replacing the real artist,

241
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:11,960
end up making the song famous
across the country.

242
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:17,080
Exactly. It's all about fate.

243
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:19,640
If someone's meant to be famous,
they will be, no matter what.

244
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:22,600
Anyway,

245
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,560
that song wasn't really right for you.

246
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:27,200
I agree with them.

247
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:34,400
Okay, I understand now.

248
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:37,880
Starting tomorrow, Poona and I

249
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:41,840
will join the office as employees
of Darathong Music.

250
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:45,440
I promise to take good care of her.

251
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:46,920
Wilai, Tharin, don't worry.

252
00:18:51,080 --> 00:18:52,560
I'll find a way

253
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:55,360
to bring out that teddy bear.

254
00:18:57,440 --> 00:19:01,000
The truth about my father
and false accusations toward you

255
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:03,400
will finally be revealed.

256
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:08,040
I'll gather the evidence

257
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:10,280
to prove everyone's innocence.

258
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:17,880
Alright, today is the anniversary
of their deaths.

259
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:20,680
Let's help organize the offerings.

260
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:32,080
Aunt Wilai, you prepared
five-spice eggs too?

261
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:35,040
Yes, five-spice eggs

262
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:38,080
are your father's favorite.

263
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:41,720
I never forget.

264
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:54,960
Alright, let's go.

265
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:26,480
PHUPHA THARARIN

266
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:38,560
NAMTHIP THARARIN

267
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:56,360
NAMTHIP THARARIN

268
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:01,000
PHUPHA THARARIN

269
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,880
That's all? You can bring more.

270
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:08,040
Fill them up.

271
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,160
FOR THE VILLAGERS OF KHOK TA YU

272
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,720
Did you wait long?

273
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:17,600
- Hello, sir.
- Hello.

274
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:20,200
The donation tent is ready.

275
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:26,480
- Hello!
- Hello!

276
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:28,440
- There's a lot of stuff.
- Yes.

277
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:31,760
Please take care of the villagers.
They might need a lot of things.

278
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:33,600
Of course.

279
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:43,920
Singha isn't needed
at this event, damn it.

280
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,280
Why?

281
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:48,040
He owns a record label.
Why don't you like him?

282
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:51,440
He's ruthless. He has his underlings
lend money with high interest rates

283
00:21:51,520 --> 00:21:53,800
and forced people
to pay ridiculous amounts.

284
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:54,840
Alright, thank you.

285
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:56,080
RICE AND SUPPLY DONATION

286
00:21:57,080 --> 00:22:00,000
Hey! Don't cut in line. Queue up!

287
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,600
Singha, don't scold them.

288
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:05,080
We're here to do good deeds,
not to create bad karma.

289
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:08,120
Sorry, I got a bit frustrated.
The heat's getting to me.

290
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:16,840
There are too many people outside.
We shouldn't be here.

291
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:20,240
- Who's out there, Teacher?
- Kamnan Pong and Singha.

292
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,320
They're here for a merit-making event,
distributing goods.

293
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:26,400
A merit making event?

294
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:31,280
Today is the anniversary
of Onanong's death.

295
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:33,720
Kamnan Pong must be here to make merit.

296
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:39,120
Then we should leave.

297
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:41,680
They shouldn't see Uncle
or Aunt Wilai here,

298
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,120
or things will escalate.

299
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:48,800
We should split up and leave separately.

300
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:50,240
It will draw attention.

301
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:54,000
Come on. Let's hurry.

302
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:55,520
Let's go.

303
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:59,280
Alright, we'll meet at the car.
If you go with me,

304
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:01,480
it'll be too risky.

305
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:03,760
Okay, Uncle.

306
00:23:20,080 --> 00:23:21,920
Thank you.

307
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,760
Thank you, sir.

308
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:27,080
Anyone in the live stream, come join us.

309
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:29,800
Miss Maria.

310
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:32,200
- That's Mr. Sornrak!
- Yeah.

311
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:34,160
Where do you live?

312
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:36,880
It's time to play the ship couple role!

313
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:41,040
Sornrak and Maria are such a cute couple!

314
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:44,200
What do I do now?

315
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:45,720
What's so hard about it?

316
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:48,160
You just need to play
the role of the angel,

317
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:51,720
- helping the poor.
- So sad.

318
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:54,320
Now the camera
will focus on you and Mr. Sornrak.

319
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:57,680
- The couple of the year!
- Exactly.

320
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:01,360
Is that a good idea, Sophie?
I've never done anything like this.

321
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,400
Really?

322
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:07,880
Don't worry, Maria. I've got you covered.

323
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:16,000
So many people. Make sure
there's enough for everyone.

324
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:21,560
Wow, she came too?

325
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,880
She looks great.

326
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:40,040
Grandma, are you fainting? Lie down.

327
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:40,960
- Grandma!
- Oh no!

328
00:24:41,040 --> 00:24:42,600
- Wait a second.
- I'm not fainting!

329
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,600
You're not? Grandma, wait. Take this.

330
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:46,560
- Help! Grandma fainted!
- Use this, Grandma!

331
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:50,560
Mr. Sornrak,
the elderly woman fainted! Hurry!

332
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:51,720
- She fainted!
- Calm down.

333
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:53,920
- Grandma fainted!
- I did not.

334
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:56,120
- I did not!
- Grandma, are you fainting?

335
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:57,800
Grandma, calm down. Lie down.

336
00:24:57,880 --> 00:25:00,800
- I'm not!
- Grandma, you fainted.

337
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:04,320
Cameraman, come here. Hurry up!

338
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:06,280
Come here, quick!

339
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:10,000
Take lots of photos
of Mr. Sornrak and Miss Maria.

340
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:12,320
The audience wants to see them
as a couple!

341
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:14,600
If you don't believe it,
check the comments.

342
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:18,160
- That's true.
- Take plenty of pictures!

343
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:20,880
The more you capture them as a couple,
the more work we'll get.

344
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:23,480
Keep shooting!

345
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:24,520
Grandma, calm down.

346
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:28,360
- Don't tense up, Grandma.
- Don't tense up. Let go.

347
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:29,880
Relax.

348
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:32,520
Let go. Relax, Grandma.

349
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:35,640
- Don't tense up. I'll give you a massage.
- Grab her hands.

350
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:43,480
Everything's set, right?

351
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,480
Okay, I'll be there in a minute.

352
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:49,240
Please excuse me for a moment.

353
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:51,160
Where are you going?

354
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:52,920
Just to the restroom.

355
00:25:57,360 --> 00:26:00,400
Hey, Singha's leaving.

356
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:02,320
I'll follow him.

357
00:26:02,840 --> 00:26:04,160
- Be careful.
- Yeah.

358
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,800
Hey, watch where you're going!

359
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:27,920
Give it to me.

360
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:37,600
Welcome to Darathong Music.

361
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,520
Phupha.

362
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:08,320
I'm happy for you

363
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,160
that you became a singer.

364
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,880
About what happened three years ago,

365
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:19,120
I…

366
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:22,160
On.

367
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,480
Here you are.

368
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:27,280
Alright.

369
00:27:27,360 --> 00:27:29,640
- Let me introduce you.
- Okay.

370
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:32,360
This is Phupha.

371
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:33,480
And this is Singha.

372
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:36,200
Singha's the winner
of the singing competition.

373
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:39,080
But he also came in second.

374
00:27:40,120 --> 00:27:41,680
And this is Onanong.

375
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:44,160
- I already know her.
- You know her?

376
00:27:46,960 --> 00:27:50,040
Tonight, I'm attending
the governor's wife's party.

377
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:52,120
Could you help pick out an outfit for me?

378
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:55,480
Of course, I'll help you choose
something beautiful.

379
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:57,040
- Let's go.
- Okay.

380
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:12,360
Why are you looking like that?

381
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:14,440
Did you know Miss On before?

382
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:16,760
No.

383
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,400
Keep in mind.

384
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:22,520
She's with Kamnan Pong now.
Everyone knows that.

385
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:27,320
I also overheard the costume girl say

386
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:29,280
that they're getting married soon.

387
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:44,080
My phone fell. Pick it up, now!

388
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:48,560
Hurry up!

389
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:02,120
If the phone breaks,
how are you going to pay for it?

390
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:05,520
Wait!

391
00:29:07,240 --> 00:29:08,360
Who are you?

392
00:29:12,040 --> 00:29:13,520
Didn't you hear me?

393
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:15,960
Who are you? What's your name?

394
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:20,200
Are you deaf or something?

395
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:23,600
You're my debtor, aren't you?

396
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:25,800
That's why you're avoiding me.

397
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:28,120
Turn around now. Show your face!

398
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,200
Turn around!

399
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:40,560
Show your face.

400
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:44,280
Show your face!

401
00:29:58,120 --> 00:29:59,160
Boss.

402
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:01,920
They're here.

403
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:05,200
- Is everyone ready?
- Yes.

404
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:08,240
Hey! Are you trying to run?

405
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:11,720
- Don't let me catch you again.
- Who is he, Boss?

406
00:30:12,800 --> 00:30:14,880
Probably one of my debtors.

407
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:17,160
As soon as he saw me,
he quickly tried to hide.

408
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:19,800
Never mind. Forget it. Let's just go.

409
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:20,880
This way, sir.

410
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:32,120
Just wait, Singha. One day,

411
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:34,920
I'll rip that mask off of you.

412
00:30:54,760 --> 00:30:55,960
It's that guy.

413
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:58,600
What's he looking for?

414
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:12,120
Good afternoon, Boss.

415
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:15,080
His name's Weerachai.
He's the big shot around the village.

416
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:18,760
I heard someone was looking for me,
saying you wanted to meet me.

417
00:31:18,840 --> 00:31:20,240
You have work for me, right?

418
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:23,960
Whether it's beating up dogs,
yelling at old people,

419
00:31:24,040 --> 00:31:26,920
bothering women, staying at the enemy's,
watching movies, listening to music,

420
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:29,600
whatever you need, I can do it.

421
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:32,520
Do you know a singer
named Sornrak Darathong?

422
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:34,200
Of course, I know him.

423
00:31:37,520 --> 00:31:39,800
Don't tell me
you want me to go beat him up?

424
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,360
Do you have the guts to do it?

425
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:48,000
How much do you want?

426
00:31:50,320 --> 00:31:51,800
If I go beat up Sornrak,

427
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:53,520
it's going to be big news.

428
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,920
I won't be able to stay around here.

429
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:59,840
I'll give you 100,000.
Take the money and get out of here.

430
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:03,120
- Okay, but…
- 120,000.

431
00:32:04,760 --> 00:32:06,600
How about 200,000?

432
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:08,920
- The thing is…
- 150,000.

433
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:11,160
If you don't want it, get out.

434
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:14,280
Pleaw, the guy who took over the job,
what's his name?

435
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:16,760
His name is Hod.
He'll be here in five minutes,

436
00:32:16,840 --> 00:32:17,800
after I call.

437
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:19,800
Okay, Boss.

438
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:22,040
150,000 is fine. That sounds good.

439
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:25,640
Just hitting Sornrak, right?
Not to kill him.

440
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:28,640
If he dies,

441
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:31,640
come back, and I'll give you 200,000.

442
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:37,200
Okay, Boss.

443
00:32:38,320 --> 00:32:39,960
I'll make sure it's done.

444
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:42,200
Here's the deposit.

445
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:45,200
Can you wire me the payment?
I don't usually take cash.

446
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:46,560
Pleaw, call Hod now.

447
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:48,960
Uh, cash is fine.

448
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:50,760
Never mind.

449
00:32:55,320 --> 00:32:56,920
If you take this job

450
00:32:58,320 --> 00:33:00,680
and the cops catch you,
trace it back to me,

451
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:04,480
you'll rot in jail.

452
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:14,120
Okay. I understand, Boss.

453
00:33:17,440 --> 00:33:19,760
Alright, I'll get going now.

454
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:28,640
Pleaw.

455
00:33:28,720 --> 00:33:31,480
- Where did you arrange to meet Singha?
- At the back of the woods.

456
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:49,760
What's that guy looking for?

457
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:51,400
MEN'S RESTROOM

458
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:55,280
What are you staring at?

459
00:33:56,640 --> 00:33:58,800
Sorry, I thought you were my friend.

460
00:34:00,120 --> 00:34:01,400
Are you some kind of pervert?

461
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:04,200
Exactly, definitely a pervert.

462
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:20,120
Yes, Uncle.

463
00:34:20,199 --> 00:34:22,440
Where are you, Poona?

464
00:34:23,400 --> 00:34:25,840
Wait a minute, Uncle.
I have something to do.

465
00:34:27,239 --> 00:34:30,320
I'll head back.
Someone might see me if I stay.

466
00:34:31,040 --> 00:34:34,120
Okay, Uncle.
I'll follow you soon. Don't worry.

467
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:50,880
This way, sir.

468
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:56,880
How's it going?

469
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:01,560
Pleaw and Boss Noo
parked their car over there.

470
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,640
They brought people with them.

471
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:12,360
Looks like they're preparing
to take us down today.

472
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:14,600
Don't worry.

473
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:17,160
If they pull any tricks,

474
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:18,280
I won't keep them around.

475
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:28,360
Good, Chart.

476
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:31,120
If things don't go as planned,

477
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:33,080
we'll bury them here.

478
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:34,000
Yes, sir.

479
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:47,120
Hello. What's up?

480
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:49,440
There's likely to be a confrontation
with Singha's group soon.

481
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:53,040
I think we should contact the local police

482
00:35:53,120 --> 00:35:55,320
to stop it before things get worse.

483
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:58,200
Okay, I'll handle it right away.

484
00:36:22,200 --> 00:36:24,760
I heard you wanted to meet me, Boss.

485
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:25,800
Yes.

486
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:28,760
I'm here to clear things up with you.

487
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:31,320
See if you're really serious
about doing business with me.

488
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:33,600
Of course, I'm serious.

489
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:36,320
Otherwise, why would I be here
meeting you today?

490
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:37,600
What about the goods I ordered?

491
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:47,360
You've had the deposit for so long.

492
00:36:48,480 --> 00:36:50,800
It's been delayed,
and I still haven't gotten the goods.

493
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:52,920
What's going on? Will I get them today?

494
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:02,040
Today?

495
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:04,840
- Probably not.
- What the hell?

496
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,560
There's been a little issue.

497
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:10,680
- Just wait a bit longer.
- I've been waiting long enough!

498
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:13,000
- Are you trying to rip me off?
- Boss.

499
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:16,080
Maybe you should watch your tone.

500
00:37:16,160 --> 00:37:17,440
Give me my money back.

501
00:37:23,080 --> 00:37:25,760
You've already paid me.
How can you take it back?

502
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:27,520
Singha!

503
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:37,120
Hey!

504
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:05,600
You want your money back?

505
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:13,440
You should ask the bullets first.

506
00:38:13,520 --> 00:38:14,400
Don't, Singha!

507
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:36,000
Hey! What are you doing here?

508
00:38:39,080 --> 00:38:40,120
‪Well…

509
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:43,320
I'm not here for anything.

510
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:45,640
- What about you? What are you spying on?
- Quiet!

511
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:49,280
Hey, are you a peeping--

512
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:51,000
Be quiet. Stay still.

513
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:16,240
‪Hey.

514
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:17,800
What's going on here?

515
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:20,360
Run! You'll get caught
in the crossfire. Go!

516
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:30,240
- Chit, take good care of Singha.
- Yes, sir.

517
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,720
Holy crap!

518
00:40:22,480 --> 00:40:24,840
- What was that noise?
- It was an explosion.

519
00:40:24,920 --> 00:40:27,760
Help me, please! I'm scared!

520
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:30,000
Don't worry, I'll help you.

521
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:31,880
You don't need to be afraid.

522
00:40:36,360 --> 00:40:37,600
What's wrong with you?

523
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:39,920
Well, you hugged me,
so I'm just helping you out.

524
00:40:40,600 --> 00:40:41,440
Don't touch me.

525
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:46,600
Help me! I don't want to die yet.
I haven't even got a husband!

526
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:49,840
Don't worry. I'll be your husband.

527
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:50,760
Good.

528
00:40:52,160 --> 00:40:54,120
You're crazy! Don't say stuff like that!

529
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:56,760
- Let's go, to the car!
- Oh no, let's go first.

530
00:40:57,840 --> 00:41:01,560
If you're gonna run this fast,
you might as well compete in a race!

531
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:03,400
- Go!
- Move!

532
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:12,120
Are you okay, Boss?

533
00:41:17,240 --> 00:41:19,240
I'm fine. Luckily I'm wearing body armor.

534
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:24,680
Hey, the police are here!

535
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:27,280
We need to get out of here.

536
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:28,320
Quick!

537
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:31,800
- Go!
- Boss.

538
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:33,040
We should leave here quickly.

539
00:41:33,800 --> 00:41:34,920
What about your dad, Sornrak?

540
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:37,880
Yeah, that's true. Where's my dad?

541
00:41:37,960 --> 00:41:40,240
Look, I think your dad can handle himself.

542
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:42,960
- Let's leave first.
- This way, sir.

543
00:41:43,040 --> 00:41:45,040
Let's go, Mr. Sornrak!

544
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:47,080
No, I can't.

545
00:41:47,160 --> 00:41:48,360
I need to find my dad.

546
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:52,600
Hey, Mr. Sornrak! Don't go!

547
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:18,160
Poona. Poona.

548
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:12,560
Dad!

549
00:43:14,480 --> 00:43:15,440
Dad!

550
00:43:17,240 --> 00:43:19,320
RESTROOM

551
00:43:19,400 --> 00:43:20,880
Dad!

552
00:43:24,360 --> 00:43:25,280
Boss!

553
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:43,440
Don't.

554
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:51,560
Don't!

555
00:44:12,120 --> 00:44:13,960
Don't chase him. Help the injured first.

556
00:44:16,640 --> 00:44:17,680
Help…

557
00:44:19,520 --> 00:44:20,560
Help me.

558
00:44:31,960 --> 00:44:33,200
Hey.

559
00:44:34,560 --> 00:44:36,440
Where are you taking my boss?

560
00:44:36,520 --> 00:44:37,680
Going for a round of golf, maybe.

561
00:44:38,880 --> 00:44:41,720
He's been stabbed.
To the hospital, obviously.

562
00:44:41,800 --> 00:44:45,240
You can't! It'll be all over the news.
Don't you know

563
00:44:45,320 --> 00:44:46,600
Sornrak is a celebrity?

564
00:44:49,680 --> 00:44:50,880
So what are we gonna do?

565
00:44:53,360 --> 00:44:54,200
Fine.

566
00:44:55,040 --> 00:44:56,080
Let's take him to the hospital.

567
00:45:12,720 --> 00:45:14,080
There's an explosion mark here.

568
00:45:16,880 --> 00:45:18,920
Over there, there are bullet marks.

569
00:45:20,920 --> 00:45:23,120
I told you not to turn on the sirens.

570
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:25,400
Look, they're all gone
because they heard us coming.

571
00:45:26,560 --> 00:45:29,840
That's a good thing.
If they were still here,

572
00:45:29,920 --> 00:45:31,840
we'd be risking our lives, Captain.

573
00:45:34,280 --> 00:45:36,400
- Who received the report?
- I did.

574
00:45:43,760 --> 00:45:45,080
Poona.

575
00:45:48,400 --> 00:45:49,800
You're okay, right?

576
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:54,360
I heard there was shooting
and even an explosion.

577
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:56,520
Yes, Uncle. I'm fine.

578
00:45:59,600 --> 00:46:02,480
Why didn't you call me?
I couldn't reach you on the phone.

579
00:46:04,480 --> 00:46:06,040
When the incident happened,

580
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:08,640
my phone hit the ground and shut off.

581
00:46:08,720 --> 00:46:10,280
So I couldn't call.

582
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:13,280
As long as you're safe, that's good.

583
00:46:15,640 --> 00:46:17,120
Who was shooting at who?

584
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:19,880
I didn't see, I just heard the sounds.

585
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:22,720
I almost got caught in the crossfire.

586
00:46:23,680 --> 00:46:24,960
But luckily,

587
00:46:25,040 --> 00:46:27,440
this silly guy pulled me away,
and we ran off.

588
00:46:27,520 --> 00:46:28,840
So, I'm okay.

589
00:46:29,960 --> 00:46:31,040
Silly guy?

590
00:46:31,680 --> 00:46:32,560
Who are you talking about?

591
00:46:36,880 --> 00:46:38,760
It's nothing, Uncle. Don't worry about it.

592
00:46:43,800 --> 00:46:47,040
I never thought something like this
would happen in our town.

593
00:46:49,480 --> 00:46:51,960
Alright, go ahead and turn your phone on.

594
00:46:52,040 --> 00:46:53,840
Call Aunt Wilai and Teacher Mueangphrai.

595
00:46:53,920 --> 00:46:55,400
They're both worried.

596
00:46:55,480 --> 00:46:56,720
Okay, Uncle.

597
00:47:06,520 --> 00:47:08,200
You're okay, right, Poona?

598
00:47:08,800 --> 00:47:10,520
I'm fine, Aunt Wilai.

599
00:47:10,600 --> 00:47:13,800
The explosion just missed me,
so don't worry about me.

600
00:47:14,400 --> 00:47:16,880
Of course I'm worried! Why wouldn't I be?

601
00:47:17,480 --> 00:47:19,840
Can I come to see you?

602
00:47:20,520 --> 00:47:22,160
Yes, Aunt Wilai.

603
00:47:23,040 --> 00:47:26,080
I'll be there soon. I'll hurry up.

604
00:47:29,920 --> 00:47:32,160
If Poona's safe, why do you need to go?

605
00:47:32,840 --> 00:47:33,960
I'm going to see her right now.

606
00:47:34,680 --> 00:47:36,680
- You're coming with me.
- What?

607
00:47:36,760 --> 00:47:39,600
- Hurry up!
- Alright, let's go!

608
00:47:47,720 --> 00:47:49,400
Have you contacted my dad yet?

609
00:47:49,480 --> 00:47:52,160
Mr. Singha is home and safe now.

610
00:47:52,240 --> 00:47:53,320
He'll come visit soon.

611
00:47:55,800 --> 00:47:57,760
And do you know

612
00:47:57,840 --> 00:47:59,560
who attacked me?

613
00:48:00,880 --> 00:48:02,320
They were wearing masks.

614
00:48:02,920 --> 00:48:04,400
I couldn't tell who they were.

615
00:48:05,480 --> 00:48:06,560
And who helped me?

616
00:48:10,080 --> 00:48:10,920
Here they are.

617
00:48:13,360 --> 00:48:14,560
Right on time.

618
00:48:16,040 --> 00:48:17,080
Someone sent for us.

619
00:48:17,760 --> 00:48:20,280
Mr. Sornrak, did you call for us?

620
00:48:21,320 --> 00:48:22,480
Yes.

621
00:48:23,360 --> 00:48:25,760
Thank you both so much for helping me.

622
00:48:26,520 --> 00:48:28,240
What are your names?

623
00:48:28,320 --> 00:48:29,680
I'm Manat.

624
00:48:30,320 --> 00:48:31,280
I'm Chaiya.

625
00:48:31,880 --> 00:48:33,560
Thank you both so much.

626
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:36,960
Chang, give them their payment.

627
00:48:41,720 --> 00:48:44,000
Oh, it's fine.

628
00:48:44,080 --> 00:48:45,920
We don't need any money.

629
00:48:46,680 --> 00:48:49,640
We helped because we don't like
seeing people hurt.

630
00:48:49,720 --> 00:48:53,000
No, I don't like people
helping me for free.

631
00:48:53,720 --> 00:48:54,960
They're hesitating.

632
00:48:55,560 --> 00:48:57,200
I think they want more money.

633
00:48:57,960 --> 00:48:58,960
Alright.

634
00:48:59,560 --> 00:49:01,280
Give them 10,000 then.

635
00:49:11,920 --> 00:49:13,160
In that case,

636
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:15,920
a different kind of reward
would be better.

637
00:49:18,560 --> 00:49:20,680
Hey, are you kidding me?

638
00:49:21,280 --> 00:49:22,720
Wanting more than what you're given?

639
00:49:22,800 --> 00:49:24,280
Hey, Chang.

640
00:49:28,680 --> 00:49:30,080
Just say what you want.

641
00:49:37,680 --> 00:49:39,680
NEXT EPISODE

642
00:49:41,800 --> 00:49:44,320
- Hey!
- Whoa, easy.

643
00:49:44,920 --> 00:49:46,040
<i>Maria came in second place.</i>

644
00:49:46,120 --> 00:49:48,440
Why did she become a singer
before the winner?

645
00:49:52,480 --> 00:49:53,760
Who took my teddy bear out?

646
00:49:54,680 --> 00:49:57,280
Poona stole your teddy bear, Mr. Singha.

647
00:51:57,840 --> 00:52:00,160
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
